# Create UX with Wireframe Workshop  

## Objective

Learn to translate business requirements into clear wireframes for development teams and stakeholders.


---

## UX vs UI Design

### UX (User Experience)

- Focus: Ease, intuitiveness, and overall usability
- Process: Understanding user needs, journey mapping

### UI (User Interface)

- Focus: Visual layout and interactive components
- Role: Makes interfaces aesthetically pleasing and usable

**Relationship**:  
UX = Structure, research, flow  
UI = Visual and interaction design  

---

## Importance of Intuitive UI

### Norman Doors Example

| Behavior | Percentage |
|----------|------------|
| Pull wrong side | 60% |
| Embarrassment | 30% |
| Correct first time | 10% |

---

## UI Design Principles

### Consistency & Clarity

- Uniform styles (colors, fonts, icons)  
- Predictable components  
- Clear CTAs and layouts  
- Eliminate clutter

### Hierarchy & Accessibility

- Highlight important items (size, contrast)  
- Keyboard-friendly, screen-reader support  
- Readable fonts and clear structure  
- System feedback (loading, selection)

---

## Eight Principles of Information Architecture (Dan Brown)

1. **Objects** – Treat content as living entities  
2. **Choices** – Limit options to reduce overwhelm  
3. **Disclosure** – Show only what's needed at each step  
4. **Exemplars** – Use examples to clarify categories  
5. **Front Doors** – Users may enter from any point  
6. **Multiple Classification** – Offer varied browsing paths  
7. **Focused Navigation** – Keep related items grouped  
8. **Growth** – Design to scale

---

## Wireframe Fundamentals

### What is a Wireframe?

- **Alignment Tool**: Aligns stakeholders early  
- **Design Blueprint**: UI layout before visual design  
- **Focus on Layout**: Not colors or images

Source: [Sketch](https://www.sketch.com/blog/wireframe-examples/)

---

## Benefits of Wireframing

- Align team early (avoid scope creep)  
- Visualize features & navigation  
- Stay user-centered  
- Quick and inexpensive changes  

---

## Key Wireframe Components

| Component | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| Header & Logo | Brand identity section at top |
| Navigation | Sidebar or top menu for structure |
| Content Areas | Placeholder blocks for actual content |
| Inputs & Controls | Buttons, dropdowns, form fields |
| Footer (Hi-Fi) | Optional; links or contact info |

Download template: [sneakpeekit.com](https://sneakpeekit.com)

---

## Wireframe Fidelity Levels

| Level | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| Low-Fidelity | Sketchy, block shapes, for ideation |
| Mid-Fidelity | Accurate spacing, grayscale, clarity |
| High-Fidelity | Pixel-accurate mockups or clickable prototypes |

---

## Wireframing Tools for PO

| Tool | Strength |
|------|----------|
| **Paper & Pencil** | Fastest for brainstorming |
| **Whiteboard & Sticky Notes** | No tech, rearrangeable |
| **Figma** ([figma.com](https://www.figma.com)) | Real-time collaboration |
| **Balsamiq** ([balsamiq.com](https://balsamiq.com)) | Non-designer friendly |
| **Miro** ([miro.com](https://miro.com)) | Infinite canvas, templates |
| **Wireframe.cc** ([wireframe.cc](https://wireframe.cc)) | Simple interface |
| **Whimsical** ([whimsical.com](https://whimsical.com)) | Browser-based, focused |

---

## Case Study – Agricultural App (B2B)

**Users**: Farmers and Buyers  
**Screens**: Dashboard, Crop Management, Product Listings, Order Management  
**Insights**:
- Weather and inventory data = top priority  
- Designers improved layout post-wireframe  

Source: [Vicky Maulana](https://vicky-maulana.medium.com/designing-effective-ui-ux-for-agricultural-apps-implementing-best-practices-and-usability-f16e0f9fc2f3)

---

## Case Study – HR/Payroll Dashboard

**Users**: HR managers, Employees  
**Screens**: Payroll summaries, Leave status  
**Insights**:
- Highlighted financial clarity  
- Wireframe drove early agreement on data layout  

Source: [Chreator Medium](https://medium.com/@chreator/paybuddy-revolutionizing-payroll-and-hr-management-ux-case-study-c8950b7daa30)

---

## Case Study – Logistics Dashboard

**Users**: Warehouse managers, Planners  
**Screens**: Order Tracking, Maps, Inventory  
**Outcome**:
- Clarified feature priorities early  
- Dashboard became intuitive  

Sources:  
- [Eleven Space](https://www.eleven-space.com/case-studies/delivery-pro)  
