---

## Best Practices – Stakeholder Alignment

- **Sketch Early**: Start in kickoff meetings  
- **Visual Consensus**: Align non-technical stakeholders  
- **Prevent Scope Creep**: Early agreement on structure  
- **Team Alignment**: Unified understanding

---

## Best Practices – Iteration & Feedback

- Review often with teams or users  
- Use paper or low-fi for early testing  
- Stay flexible and revise as needed  
- Track changes for documentation  

---

## Best Practices – Handoff & Consistency

- Annotate components (e.g., “dropdown - select country”)  
- Use layout grids or templates  
- Export design specs from tools like Figma or Sketch  
- Create screen-to-requirement maps  

Source: [Adobe XD Ideas](https://xd.adobe.com/ideas/process/wireframing/benefits-of-annotating-wireframes/)



